<br>
The door to Vex Thal is similar. But instead of there being a line, there is a door, and opening that door makes you zone. The added geometry behind it is either just to finish the geometry or to prevent people from falling through the world if they manage to get behind it.<br>
<br>
And let me say this now and say it loud...<br>
<br>
<h3>VEX THAL EXISTS<br>
<br>
There are zone and soundfiles for it, they have all the information you need for a zone. There is ZERO reason for VI to go through all the trouble of making the zone files and not have the zone there. So please refrain from the "It's not in the game" rumors. :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uumian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Umian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/2/02 5:07:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9316.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: MOST zones are like this. Examples...</span><hr size=1> And in some fun zones, mobs like to play around in the geometry past the zone. That's always fun, having stuff run back there.<br>
